    "[INT 12] • Down-to-earth expectations, no promises • \"I thought the program was interesting... Knowing what's in it, I'd do it again today...",
    "In the beginning, you don't make any promises.",
    "In the program, it says 'learning to live with chronic pain', but there's no promise; it doesn't say: 'Hey, when you get to the eighth week, you're pain-free'.\"",
    "[INT 10] • \"But I think the program doesn't apply to me... You know, it's like, geez, I thought I would discover something amazing.",
    "It's been four years now, I've seen three internists, lots of doctors, and I went to a maxillofacial specialist back in September, and we're trying to figure it out, but nobody knows what it is."
  ],
